  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6563.79 sitting below the GEX flip at 6576, dealers are positioned to buy dips and sell rallies in this PIN regime, creating a strong mean-reversion environment toward the 6575-6580 zone where massive positive gamma walls (+39.5B and +21.7B) will act as magnets. The recent GEX surge combined with spot trading below flip means dealers are likely net buying here to hedge their long gamma positions, providing natural support. Watch 6550 as the key downside level where dealers flip to buying mode (-16.2B negative gamma), while any push above 6576 flip should see increasing dealer selling pressure into the 6580-6585 gamma wall complex.",
